    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-01T16:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-01T16:35:00-05:00" n="845"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d845">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/6–3054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d845fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_FWD1"
                            >Fisher</persName> of <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_WE1">WE</gloss>. Repeated to Saigon as telegram 15 and to
                        Geneva as telegram <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 506.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>limit distribution</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-01T17:35:00-04:00"
                            >July 1, 1954—5:35 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Re <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 5117.<note n="2" xml:id="d845fn2"
                        >In telegram 5117 from Paris, June 30, Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName> reported on a discussion between
                        British Ambassador to France <persName corresp="#p_JSHMG1">Sir Gladwyn
                            Jebb</persName> and Premier <persName corresp="#p_MFP1"
                            >Mendès-France</persName> on June 30. Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_JSHMG1">Jebb</persName> indicated <persName
                            corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendès-France</persName> had confirmed that
                        negotiations with the Viet Minh at Geneva were stalled. He said <persName
                            corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendès-France</persName> was perplexed by a reference
                        in a British note to a “‘line running generally west from Dong Hoi’ as
                        possible partition line for while Dong Hoi is approximately at 17.5 degrees
                        French had been holding out for 18th Parallel in face Viet Minh wanting
                        13th.” On the question of elections, Ambassador <persName
                            corresp="#p_JSHMG1">Jebb</persName> quoted <persName corresp="#p_MFP1"
                            >Mendès-France</persName> “as stating that the Viet Minh wanted them to
                        be held in six months but that the French were taking the position that they
                        should be delayed for a year after final settlement and withdrawal of troops
                        had been achieved. This, as presently envisaged, would mean a year and half
                        to two years from now.” (751G.00/6–3054)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Partition line taken from Five Power Conference report and <persName
                            corresp="#p_PVD1">Dong</persName>-Hoi used as point of reference to
                        avoid confusion between two systems, French and English, of parallels.
                        Actual line thought of forms triangular promontory with apex at about 20th
                        parallel (French system).</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Implication paragraph on timing elections due to use of expression “final
                        settlement and troop withdrawal” is that <persName corresp="#p_MFP1"
                            >Mendes-France</persName> thinking of withdrawing entire French
                        Expeditionary Corps from all of Viet Nam within next six months.
                        “Withdrawal”, on other hand, could mean deployment into agreed regroupment
                        areas. Does <persName corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes</persName> seek agreement
                        allowing reassembly in retained Viet Nam those Expeditionary Troops
                        withdrawn from Tonkin and indefinite maintenance in retained Viet Nam of
                        French forces now stationed there or are French prepared agree withdraw from
                        all Viet Nam all French forces within matter of months? This requires full
                        and urgent clarification.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName> with <persName
                            corresp="#p_MFP1">Mendes</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_JUA1"
                            >Johnson</persName> with <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName>
                        should urgently seek such clarification.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
